Minor revisions were gathered by Ruth Osimk-Teasdale and Michael Radeka and corrections were made by Ruth Osimk-Teasdale. notesStmt.note: This meeting at the university language center involves nine speakers who work at different language schools in Europe and are involved in a joint program dealing with the teaching of languages in relation to food. They meet in order to discuss the success of, and problems encountered with, their individual projects. At the beginning S1 finishes a presentation of the project she organized, which took place the night before. S1 functions as the chair of the meeting, but S2, who takes notes during the meeting and is the administrative advisor of the project, is fairly prominent, too. A large part of the conversation takes place among S1, S2, S3 and S4. The meeting ends by the speakers forming two groups to discuss details.

namespace.tagUsage: Used to mark a stretch of speech commonly preceded and followed by a pause or by a change of speaker. Auis, however, not required to be bounded by a pause or a change of speaker, nor does it represent a turn in a conversation analytic sense. At a minimum, auis some phonetic production or noise made by a given speaker or a group of speakers.
Used to mark speech which cannot be transcribed with certainty, because it is difficult to hear or understand for the transcriber.
